{"ASK":[{"def":"To request; to seek to obtain by words; to petition; to solicit; - - often with of, in the sense of from, before the person addressed.","pos":""},{"def":"To require, demand, claim, or expect, whether by way of remuneration or return, or as a matter of necessity; as, what price do you ask Ask me never so much dowry.","pos":""}],"ASKANCE":[{"def":"O, how are they wrapped in with infamies That from their own misdeeds askance their eyes! Shak.","pos":""}],"ASKER":[{"def":"One who asks; a petitioner; an inquirer.","pos":""}],"ASKEW":[{"def":"Awry; askance; asquint; oblique or obliquely; -- sometimes indicating scorn, or contempt, or entry.","pos":""}],"ASKING":[{"def":"The act of inquiring or requesting; a petition; solicitation.","pos":""},{"def":"The publishing of banns.","pos":""}]}